<TEXT>
   Chrysler Corp. -- The size of its Auburn Hills Trust
guaranteed exchangeable certificates, due May 1, 2020, was
increased to $1.1 billion from $1 billion because of strong
demand. Earlier, the offering had been increased to $1
billion from $800 million. Chrysler said the $1.1 billion
offering is the largest 30-year debt deal offered by an
investment grade-rated industrial company. Details of the
offering, priced at par to yield 12 3/8%, were announced
Thursday.
   Mountain States Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. -- $100 million
