Delivery is scheduled for May 8 with interest accruing May 1.
Mountain States Telephone is a unit of U S West Inc.
   Northwest Bell Telephone Co. -- $75 million of notes, due
May 1, 2000, was priced at 99 with a 9 1/2% coupon to yield
9.658%. The non-callable notes were priced at a spread of 60
basis points above the Treasury's 10-year note. Rated
double-A-3 by Moody's and double-A-minus by S&amp;P, the issue
will be sold through underwriters led by Morgan Stanley &amp; Co.
Delivery is set for May 8 with interest accruing May 1.
Northwest Bell Telephone is a unit of U S West Inc.
                                                                                                       

                         MORTGAGES
                                                                                                       

   Federal National Mortgage Association -- $300 million of
real estate mortagage investment conduit securities was
offered in 10 classes by Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc. The
offering, Series 1990-59, was structured with coupons ranging
from 7% to 10%. Pricing information was not immediately
available. The collateral consists of Fannie Mae's 10%
securities with an underlying weighted average coupon rate of
10.7% and weighted average remaining term to maturity of 29.9
years. The issue settles June 29.
                                                                                                       

                          AGENCY
                                                                                                       

