<HL>
   Oak Industries to Sell Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
05/01/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A12
</SO>
<CO>
   OAK
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   SAN DIEGO, Calif. -- Oak Industries Inc. said it reached
an agreement in principle to sell its Oak Communications Inc.
subsidiary to the Lorain Group, a San Diego-based investment
firm.
   Terms of the transaction weren't disclosed, and the sale
is expected to close by late June if all conditions are met.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   William S. Antle III, Oak's president and chief executive
officer, said the sale would help the parent company improve
return of its operations and fund acquisitions. Oak
Communications is a maker of cable and setellite
communications equipment whose principal manufacturing plant
is in Taipei, Taiwan. Oak Industries is an electronic parts
maker.
</TEXT>
