<HL>
   Carter-Wallace Buys
   Hygeia Sciences Unit
   From Tambrands Inc.
</HL>
<DATE>
05/01/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CAR TMB
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Carter-Wallace Inc. said it acquired Hygeia
Sciences Inc., which markets First Response at-home pregnancy
and ovulation test kits, from Tambrands Inc. Terms weren't
disclosed.
   Carter-Wallace, a marketer of toiletries and
pharmaceutical products, said that the First Response will
complement its existing line of Answer at-home pregnancy and
ovulation test kits and will make it the leading marketer of
such kits. Tambrands said that First Response, with annual
sales of about $28 million, has about a 25% market share of
the in-home test kit market, while Answer has about a 10%
market share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Tambrands, based in Lake Success, N.Y., is a maker of
personal-care products. In selling its Hygeia Science
subsidiary, Tambrands said that it has completed its plan to
divest noncore businesses to concentrate on marketing Tampax
tampons and Maxithins sanitary pads. Last February, Tambrands
sold its cosmetics subsidiary, Physicians Formula Cosmetics
Inc., to Pierre Farbre, a French-based cosmetics company.
</TEXT>
