<HL>
   BC Gas to Sell Preferred
</HL>
<DATE>
05/01/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C16
</SO>
<CO>
   T.BCG
</CO>
<LP>
   VANCOUVER, British Columbia -- BC Gas Inc., a natural-gas
utility, said it agreed to sell to Scotia-McLeod Inc., a
Toronto securities dealer, 20 million Canadian dollars
(US$17.2 million) of preferred shares.
   BC Gas said proceeds will be used to reduce debt. The
dividend rate on the shares, which will be cumulative,
redeemable and non-convertible, will be 9% annually for the
first five years, and set by negotiation subsequently, it
said.
</LP>
